  "elapsed_s": 6.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And arriving in Israel was a tremendous celebration.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Because you know, we are, we come again and a few days before, that we were drowned.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And they-- in Israel when we arrived, they took us to a, a center, a school all the kids.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And then again, different organizations were trying to get as many children to their side.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "But supposedly was up to the children.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And I had relatives, and many had, that came to visit us.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And we used to discuss it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "But anyway, I selected to go to Mikveh Israel, which was one of the oldest agriculture schools in Israel, which I made a good choice.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The other choices were to go to [INAUDIBLE] [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] to [?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Mizrahi ?] [INAUDIBLE] Israel.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Any organization had the right into your children and try to influence, influence them to join them with promises, you know?",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The big difference was that if you went to [INAUDIBLE], you went to [INAUDIBLE] kibbutz, which normally they had their own school.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I was not religious, but I was, you know, religious-oriented.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I figure, I had my background.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I would like to go to a, a religious school, which was Mikveh Israel.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Some went to more orthodox, which I was very happy.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I feel that that school gave me my base education in my life, to go out in the free world and manage-- excellent education, excellent supervision.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Being at that school, I, I joined the Haganah.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We-- general education, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] a lot of agriculture, which the purpose of that school was to become farmer, to join a kibbutz, moshav, moshavim.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I did specialize in agriculture equipment, mechanical equipment.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
